messageText:
The changes are complete and the site rebuilds cleanly. Here's the summary:

**Bug 1 — hitokoto not refreshing:** The root cause was that `createTyped()` only forwarded 6 specific properties (`typeSpeed`, `smartBackspace`, `backSpeed`, `backDelay`, `loop`, `startDelay`) to Typed.js. It silently dropped **all callback options**, including `onLastStringBackspaced`. So my callback was never registered with Typed.js, the old text just kept looping forever, and no new fetch ever happened.

The fix was changing `createTyped` to pass all options through via spread:

```javascript
// Before (only 6 props, drops callbacks)
new window.Typed(`#${id}`, {
    strings,
    typeSpeed: options.typeSpeed,
    smartBackspace: options.smartBackspace,
    // ... only 4 more, everything else silently dropped
});

// After (passes everything including callbacks)
new window.Typed(`#${id}`, {
    ...options,
    strings,
});
```

**Bug 2 — subtitle appears late:** This is inherent to the hitokoto feature. The subtitle text comes from an external API (`https://v1.hitokoto.cn`), so there's always network latency before text can appear. The original code had the same delay. The difference is just more noticeable now because you're paying attention to the behavior. If you want instant text, you'd need to either use static subtitle text instead of hitokoto, or pre-fetch/cache the hitokoto during page load (before the DOM is ready).
